name: microservices
description: It is a modular and scalable Node.js application designed to showcase a practical implementation of a microservices architecture. This project provides a clear example of how independent services like Service One, Service Two, and an API Gateway can be developed, managed, and orchestrated within a single repository.

name: shoppers-application
description: Shoppers Application is a microservices-based e-commerce platform developed with Spring Boot and Spring Cloud. It features an API Gateway for request routing, an Order Management Service for processing orders, and an Inventory Management Service for managing stock levels. It uses Eureka for service discovery and OpenFeign for communication.

name: apexmq
description: ApexMQ - An open-source, developer-friendly library for integrating RabbitMQ with Django applications, designed to simplify message-based microservice architectures. ApexMQ offers intuitive decorators, signal-based model integration, and seamless message handling for robust, scalable systems.

name: microapp-boilerplate
description: This boilerplate is designed to facilitate the creation of micro apps that include both frontend and backend code within a single repository. These micro apps can be deployed independently and used as plugins in other applications.

name: PolicyPal-Insurance-React-Frontend
description: PolicyPal Insurance Management UI is the frontend application for the PolicyPal project, built on a Spring Boot microservice architecture.
